\subsection{Experimental Results}

This section presents results and demonstrates cross-referencing capabilities across different files.

\subsubsection{Verification of Equations}

We have previously defined several important equations:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Equation~\ref{eq:einstein} shows the relationship between energy and mass
    \item Equation~\ref{eq:quadratic} provides the solution for quadratic equations
    \item Equation~\ref{eq:euler} demonstrates the beauty of mathematical relationships
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{Compilation Testing}

This multi-file document tests several critical features:

\begin{theorem}
If the compilation system correctly processes all files, then:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item All \texttt{\textbackslash input} commands resolve correctly
    \item Custom style packages are loaded and available
    \item Bibliography citations work across files
    \item Cross-references work between different sections
\end{enumerate}
\end{theorem}

\subsection{Bibliography Integration}

The bibliography system has been tested with multiple citations:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Classic \TeX{} documentation: \cite{knuth1984}
